summary: I know you haven’t written for a while but I enjoyed your writing and wanted to send you a request. Which characters, couples...
question: I know you haven’t written for a while but I enjoyed your writing and wanted to send you a request. Which characters, couples and fandoms do you write for?
answer:
Hey :). Yes, it’s been a while, I have been busy. But thanks for your message. I am open to requests whenever. The fandoms I write for are:

  • Game of Thrones/ASOIAF
  • Lord of the Rings
  • Marvel

To be honest, these are the only 3 that I really understand the characters in and feel that I can do justice to them when writing. As for characters, I will pretty much write about any character. With couples, I am a bit more picky, because the ones that I am indifferent too, I therefore would not want to write for them because I will not portray their relationship right, and I only feel comfortable with writing the ones that I personally really like myself, because I am more invested in their relationship.

  • Jon/Sansa
  • Ned/Catelyn
  • Sansa/Theon
  • Grey Worm/Missandei
  • Jaime/Brienne
  • Arya/Gendry
  • Aragorn/Arwen
  • Faramir/Eowyn
  • Tony/Pepper
  • Peter/Gamora
  • Vision/Wanda

There are a few more, but these are the ones that I am most confident writing. If I am doing a bit multi chapter story, then I will include more, even those not on the list. For example, I was considering doing a LOTR High School AU type fic and would therefore include other couples, and even make a few couples up myself. Really though, just message me with the fic you want writing, I am likely to say yes to you :)

summary: Alright now that I’ve calmed down I don’t think Maisie’s giving spoilers like that, because if she’s doing it without realising...
body:
Alright now that I’ve calmed down I don’t think Maisie’s giving spoilers like that, because if she’s doing it without realising at least Lena wouldn’t join in, there’s honestly no way they would let them do it.

So I reckon they are soft-trolling. But that has to mean like she’s standing among the fallen ones in her final scene, right? With the blood and everything, it has to mean that she’s in a battle/ murder spree of some sort. Does that mean she’s the only one standing among the list of people she intended to kill? It can’t be that she’s the only Stark alive though. God I want ANSWERS

summary: Family Tree Time
body:
Family Tree Time


Podrick Payne is the son of ↓

Tyrion Lannister and Brienne of Tarth


Godson / Nephew of ↓

Ser Bronn of the (fucking) Blackwater

(there are soooooooo many good scenes with him and Bronn)

Step son and nephew of ↓

Jaime Lannister


Brother to ↓

Arya Stark


  • He’s Jaime’s stepson because Jaime and Brienne are clearly married.
  • He’s Arya’s brother because Arya is the Hound and Brienne’s murder child and therefore they are half siblings.
  • Him being Bronn’s godson/nephew is just a given tbh
